{"key":"processedPost-8995928","value":{"id":8995928,"first":8994760,"last":8997206,"when":1222571981,"utime":"09/28/08 06:19 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />The advice was to take the perlite down to 2 inches.</blockquote><br />Bad advice.&nbsp; I recommend 5 inches, but that doesn't mean that six inches is bad.&nbsp; In fact, using more will let you go longer without having to replenish the moisture in the perlite.<br />Another trick is to rake the perlite with your fingers every week or two to fluff it up.&nbsp; This will free up more surface area to evaporate moisture.<br />99% humidity is perfect.&nbsp; Don't let anyone tell you to fix what obviously isn't broken.<br />RR","title":"Re: Too much perlite.. really?"}}